messages.content: As an AI assistant, my role is to meticulously analyze criminal justice documents and extract information about law enforcement personnel. The response will contain: 1) The name of a law enforcement personnel. The individual's name must be prefixed with one of the following titles to be in law enforcement: Detective, Sergeant, Lieutenant, Captain, Deputy, Officer, Patrol Officer, Criminalist, Technician, Coroner, or Dr. Please prefix the name with 'Officer Name: '. I will derive this data from the following paragraph: Investi9ator Lewis, with the ass1stance of Chauffer Rodney Robinson, rolled the decedent 0ver and placed her in a body bag. Technician Muhammad phot0graphed and collected the spent casing, which was identified as a

9mm Luger at 12:31am. Sergeant McMullen advised Detective Morton that there was a blood trail from the interior hallway to North Derbignay Street. Crime Lab Technician Tamika Rogers, Unit 5137, conducted gunshot residue tests on both Darceleen Commodore and Earlitta Taylor at the Homicide Office. Coroner's Office Day Records from Detective David Trehan officially classified the shooting deaths of Patrice Commodore and Jessie Bibbins as Homicides. Detective Aucoin located a set of keys, which were hanging from a keybox in the living room of the residence. He then locked and secured the residence and placed a seal from the Orleans Parish Coroner's Office on the door. Detective Morton met with witness Darceleen Commodore at her residence regarding her encounter with Reynell Payne. Detective Morton received a copy of the Fifth District Incident Report. The Crime Lab began processing the scene directed by Detective Ryan Aucoin. Detective Sergeant Chris Robert manned Unit 520. Officers Phil Burras & Quincy Broaden manned Unit 507. Officers Nate Addison & Glen Hewitt manned Unit 516. Detective Gregory Johnson manned Unit 546. Detective Jason McGee manned Unit 1571. Detective Ananie Mitchell manned Unit 1574. Detective Melvin McCullum manned Unit 1576. Detective Pratt of the Homicide Section handled a scene on Mazant Street. Detective Mathews compiled photographic line-ups at the Homicide Office. Scientific Criminal Investigations Division Officer Gary Sallienger was involved in the scene sketch. Orleans Parish Coroner's Office Investigator Parnell Williams processed the scene by Orleans Parish Coroner's Office.
Identify each individual in the transcript, by name, who are directly referred to as officers, sergeants, lieutenants, captains, detectives, homicide officers, and crime lab personnel.
